main event: A witness observed an unidentified object in the sky over Fillmore, Illinois on January 29, 1967.
interesting points: The object was similar in size to a large helicopter, but without any particular sound.
The object moved slowly and hovered over a woodland area.
The object produced a fine mist or yellowish fog at intervals, but there was no odor or sound noted.
The object's lights were contained within it, rather than focused on the ground or trees.
The object moved off slowly, without any perceptible sound or motion, and its distinctive silhouette was lost as it descended behind the trees.
sighted object: large, silent, hovering object with colored lights
witnesses: multiple witnesses, including people on the road and in the distance
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
